import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['job'] = data['job'].astype('category')
    data = data.groupby('job').sum().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by='count', ascending=False)
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    ax = sns.barplot(x="job", y="count", data=data, palette="Blues_d")
    ax.set_xticklabels(ax.get_xticklabels(), rotation=90, ha="right")
    plt.title('What is the most common job in the dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.axhline(y=data['count'].max(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Max Count: {:.2f}'.format(data['count'].max()))
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['year'])
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    sns.set(style="whitegrid")
    chart = sns.catplot(x="job", y="count", hue="sex", data=data, kind="bar", height=10, aspect=1.5)
    chart.set_xticklabels(rotation=90)
    plt.title('What is the gender distribution across different jobs?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['job_count'] = pd.to_numeric(data['job_count'], errors='coerce')
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='job_count', kde=True, color='blue')
    plt.axvline(data['job_count'].median(), color='red', label='Median: {:.2f}'.format(data['job_count'].median()))
    plt.legend()
    plt.title('What is the distribution of job counts?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
